Request: <%= @info_request.title %>
Submitted: <%= simple_date(@info_request.created_at) %>
Days elapsed: <%= ((Time.now - @info_request.created_at) / 1.day).floor %> calendar days

Under the Code on Access to Information:
- Departments should provide an initial response or interim reply within 10 calendar days
- The target completion time is 21 calendar days
- The maximum processing time is 51 calendar days in exceptional circumstances

What you can do now:

1. SEND A REMINDER
   You can send a polite reminder to the department through <%= site_name %>:
   <%= request_url(@info_request) %>

2. REQUEST AN INTERNAL REVIEW
   If the department is significantly overdue or unresponsive, you can request an internal review by a senior officer:
   <%= new_request_followup_url(@info_request.url_title, internal_review: '1') %>

3. COMPLAIN TO THE OMBUDSMAN
   If an internal review doesn't resolve the issue, you can lodge a complaint with The Ombudsman (申訴專員):
   https://www.ombudsman.hk/

The Code on Access to Information is an administrative code that governs how Hong Kong government departments handle information requests. While it is not legislation, departments are expected to comply with its provisions.

